The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, November 15, 2002  Allodium, Ardency shine 
 BY OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT				 										Calcutta: Allodium. Ardency, Rescue Act, River Melody and Abridge were impressive when following horses worked on Thursday.				 										Outer sand track 				 										1,400m: Smart Ruler (Merchant) and Royal Command (Asghar) in 1-46s; (400m) 29s. They were stretched out as the former was 2 ls better. 				 										1,200m: Assertive Dancer (Merchant) and Discomatic (Asghar) in 1-25s; (400m) 29s. They were stretched out as the former finished ahead by a length. Allodium (Islam), Alcalde (C. Alford) and Alternator (Rabani) in 1-23s; (400m) 28s. Alcalde joined at 800m but failed by two lengths to beat Allodium. Alternator weas outclassed. Primaticcio (Asghar) and Nationalistic (Merchant) in 1-27s; (400m) 27s. Former impressed while finishing ahead by a length. Ardency (C. Alford) and Sadaf (Rabani) in 1-26s; (400m) 30s. They worked well as they finished level. 				 										800m: Ace of Spades (Salim K.) in 56s; (400m) 28s. Rescue Act (Salam) and Alkido (Rabani) in 57s; (400mj) 29s. Former moved well while finishing ahead by 2 ls. Sanctified Star (Merchant) in 56s; (400m) 28s. Fit. Star Of Ring (R. Ahmed) and Terrificco (Gurang) in 58s; (400m) 29s. They were easy as they levelled. Mister Twister (Rabani) and Silk Route (Islam) in 57s; (400m) 29s. They were easy as they levelled. They are two-year-olds. Crowning Moment (G. Singh) in 55s; (400m) 29s. Fit. Blushing Queen (Upadhya) and Brighter Future (A. P. Singh) in 1-2s; (400m) 29s. They were level. They are two- year-olds. Forest Ridge (Gurang) and Bright And Clear (Salim K.) in 1-0s; (400m) 30s. They were easy as they levelled. River Melody (A. P. Singh) and Soviet Port (Yadav) in 55s; (400m) 28s. Former was a length better. Note former. Bold Chieftan (Merchant) in 1-3s; (400m) 31s. Easy.				 										600m: Bold Apparel (Merchant) in 43s; (400m) 28s. Moved well.				 										Sand track				 										1,200m: King Crest (G. Singh) and Say It Lord (Surender) in 1-28s; (400m) 29s. They were level.				 										800m: Aurelia (Rutherford) in 53s; (400m) 25s. Abridge (Rutherford) in 50s; (400m) 24s. Impressed. Black Majik Woman (Chisty) and Lawyers Love (Rutherford) in 51s; (400m) 24s. Former 4 ls better. Royal Account (Chisty) and Richie Rich (Rutherford) in 1-0s; (400m) 27s. They were level. They are Two-year-olds.
